  "prompt": "Which US credit card charges no foreign transaction fees?",
  "response": "Many U.S. credit cards do not charge foreign transaction fees, which can be a significant advantage for travelers. Some popular options include:\n\n1. **Chase Sapphire Preferred\u00ae Card** - Offers travel rewards and no foreign transaction fees.\n2. **Chase Sapphire Reserve\u00ae** - Premium card with no foreign transaction fees and enhanced travel benefits.\n3. **Capital One Venture Rewards Credit Card** - Offers miles on travel purchases and no foreign transaction fees.\n4. **Capital One QuicksilverOne Cash Rewards Credit Card** - A cash-back card with no foreign transaction fees.\n5. **Discover it\u00ae Miles** - Earns miles on purchases and has no foreign transaction fees.\n6. **American Express Gold Card** - Offers rewards on dining and travel with no foreign transaction fees.\n7. **Citi Premier\u00ae Card** - Provides travel rewards and no foreign transaction fees.\n\nWhen considering a credit card, it\u2019s important to evaluate other aspects as well, such as rewards programs, annual fees, and other benefits that suit your spending habits.",
